        +
        
          
            1
            
              a
              
                n
              
            
          
        
        .
      
    
    {\displaystyle a_{n+1}={\frac {a_{n}+{\frac {2}{a_{n}}}}{2}}={\frac {a_{n}}{2}}+{\frac {1}{a_{n}}}.}
  The more iterations through the algorithm (that is, the more computations performed and the greater "n"), the better the approximation. Each iteration roughly doubles the number of correct digits. Starting with 
  
    
      
        
          a
          
            0
          
        
        =
        1
      
    
    {\displaystyle a_{0}=1}
  , the results of the algorithm are as follows:

