  The convergents p/q formed by truncating this representation form a sequence of fractions that approximate the square root of two to increasing accuracy, and that are described by the Pell numbers (i.e., p2 − 2q2 = ±1). The first convergents are: 1/1, 3/2, 7/5, 17/12, 41/29, 99/70, 239/169, 577/408 and the convergent following p/q is p + 2q/p + q. The convergent p/q differs from 
  
    
      
        
          
            2
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\sqrt {2}}}
   by almost exactly 1/2√2q2, which follows from:

  
    
      
        
